body_html:
I figured out the root-cause.
It's because the dimension of Placeholder of the frozen model is (1, 299, 299, 3) and it can' be modified once been generated.
The solution is to regenerate a binary graph.pbtxt of the model with input placeholder(?, 299, 299, 3), then freeze it and use tensorrt to optimize it.

body:
I figured out the root-cause.
It's because the dimension of Placeholder of the frozen model is (1, 299, 299, 3) and it can' be modified once been generated.
The solution is to regenerate a binary graph.pbtxt of the model with input placeholder(?, 299, 299, 3), then freeze it and use tensorrt to optimize it.
